node.title: Northern Territory records 3 new COVID cases, infant taken to Royal Darwin Hospital
node.alt: Road signage on the side of a highway intersection in the Northern Territory.
node.description: The three new infections are all connected to known cases from Katherine and Robinson River, while authorities say a man who tested positive yesterday contracted the virus from a fish and chip shop exposure site.
node.content: ["The Northern Territory has recorded three\u00a0new local cases of COVID-19 overnight, Chief Minister Michael Gunner says.", "All are close contacts of known cases, and one is an infant from Robinson River.", "The other two cases are a\u00a0man in his 40s who received one vaccine dose and identified as a close contact, and an unvaccinated woman in her 20s.", "The Territory's cluster now stands at 40 cases.", "Mr Gunner said 1,149 COVID tests were conducted in Katherine yesterday.", "\"We are confident all residents in Warlpiri Camp have now been tested,\" Mr Gunner said.", "\"We are now confident that all residents in Rockhole and Warlpiri Camp and Binjari, I believe, have now received their first dose of the vaccine.\"", "All the test results from Rockhole have come back negative so far.", "Mr Gunner said one of the local cases identified yesterday, a man in his 60s, was believed to be a close contact from the Captain Jack Fish and Chips exposure site.", "The Bicentennial Road catchment area continues to return positive wastewater results and the Katherine golf course catchment has returned a positive wastewater result from Saturday.", "\"This indicates there continues to be positive cases in Katherine that are yet to be detected,\" Mr Gunner said.", "\"Testing continues to be crucial. Please keep getting tested.\"", "The close contact numbers now stand at 460. Of those,\u00a0453 are located and isolated.", "Those contacts have returned 406 negative results so far.", "The close contact exposure site list now includes the Eastside Mini Mart on Monday, November 15 between 8:05am and 8:15am.", "Fourteen casual contact sites spread over Katherine have been added overnight.", "Katherine will have to be in some form of lockdown or lockout until December 4, Mr Gunner said.", "\"That doesn't mean the whole period will be locked down,\" he said.", "\"We will transition to a lockout at some point. I cannot give you any more comfort on when that will be.\"", "Acting Chief Health Officer Charles Pain said the child was in hospital in a stable condition.", "He said the young woman in her 20s was in the Centre for National Resilience and has \"significant respiratory symptoms, but she's not requiring hospitalisation\".", "The man in his 40s tested negative twice before returning a positive test yesterday, he said.", "Dr Pain said the recent positive wastewater samples meant authorities would continue to focus their efforts in the Bicentennial area.", "NT Police Commissioner Jamie Chalker said people\u00a0in locked-down areas had\u00a0been \"really compliant\".", "\"We have had the Australian Defence Force mobilised \u2026 so we're very appreciative of that support,\" he said.", "\"And that will certainly make our ability to respond more broadly to ensuring that people are compliant within the Katherine area.\"", "Commissioner Chalker said plans were underway to help Darwin or Alice Springs residents who had\u00a0been caught up in the Katherine lockdown to return home.", "He urged those people to get a COVID test immediately.", "More to come."]
